content.text: Calculate the number of women who did not finish the race, the number of men who did not finish the race, and the number of men who finished the race, based on the following steps: No. of women who did not finish race = $0.2 \times 315 = 63$. No. of men who did not finish race = $230 - 63 = 167$. No. of men who finished race = $(1050 - 315) - 167 = 568$.
